Former National Chairman of All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA), Senator Victor Umeh, has implored Nigerians to prioritise the acts of showing love towards one another and offering self­less service to humanity for the sake of societal growth and development. Umeh, who represented Anambra Central Senatori­al District in the 8th Senate for 17 months, made the call in his New Year message to Nigerians. He noted that engaging in acts of love and selflessness would go a long way in ensur­ing peace and unity among the citizens. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He further stated that be­ing alive to witness the New Year was only a privilege, and therefore, should be enough reason to roll out the drums for celebration and in thanks­giving to God, stressing that there are many who may have prayed fervently to see 2021, but did not make it. His words: “It is with great joy that I wish to congratulate everyone who was able to see the year 2020 come to an end and the beginning of a brand New Year 2021 which opti­mistically, will be better and prosperous. Kwara Announces January 11 For Schools’ Resumption Improved Budgeting System Will Curb Deficit Financing – Economist “It is obvious that the pre­vious year was not without many untoward situations ranging from the adverse effects of the novel Corona­virus pandemic to economic instabilities as well as the breakdown of law and order during the #Endsars protest by Nigerian youths. Indeed, being alive and healthy to see this New Year is a privilege and enough reason to cele­brate because many could not make it. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION